records.addlTxt: 10:04 AM Defendant Tiffani L Langreck appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Gavin Grubofski in court for Tiffani L Langreck.  Prosecuting attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea/sentencing hearing on October 3, 2022 at 10:00 am.

4:30 PM Defendant Tiffani L Langreck in court, in custody.  Attorney Nathan T. Oswald in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Laura Federico in court for Tiffani L Langreck. 
Terry Endries appears by video, is sworn and questioned by Attorney Oswald. He is a police officer with the Marshfield Police Department. On 7/12/22, he stopped a vehicle for a traffic violation. Jason Kluth was the driver of the vehicle. They were on the lookout for the vehicle due to a retail theft at Fleet Farm earlier. Video showed defendant getting into the vehicle that was stopped. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom.  Jason Kluth gave permission to search a backpack in the vehicle. He located a syringe with brown substance in it and a baggie with a substance in it. It tested positive for methamphetamine. Jason Kluth indicated that the bag belonged to Ms. Langreck. Attorney Federico cross-examines witness.  Attorney Oswald redirects.  
Attorney Oswald makes statement. 
Attorney Federico makes statement.
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Not guilty plea. Attorney Federico is requesting that cash bond be modified to signature bond.  State is opposed.  Court denies motion to modify bond. Bond is continued.
Final pre-trial scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 10:00 am.
